article.headline: Prairie View 69, Alabama State 42
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Malcolm Campbell scored 18 points to lead Alabama State to a 68-42 win over Prairie View on Monday night. Alexander Oliver added nine points for the Hornets (5-12, 3-5 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Joshua Thompson scored 14 points and Tyrone Nelson added 12 for Prairie View (3-14, 3-5). Alabama State built a 29-16 halftime lead, then shot 59 percent in the second half to keep the Panthers at bay. The Hornets made 6 of 11 3-point attempts, including all four after halftime. Prairie View shot only 33 percent and missed all nine 3-point shots. The Panthers had only two assists and turned the ball over 22 times.
